# Environment & Security

## Environment Files
- .env.dev / .env.staging / .env.prod — ALL gitignored.
- flutter_dotenv reads per-flavor file at startup.
- Never String.fromEnvironment() outside core/config/app_config.dart.
- CI/CD: inject secrets via Codemagic environment groups — never committed.

## Secrets Storage
- API keys, tokens, passwords: FlutterSecureStorage ONLY.
- Never SharedPreferences for anything sensitive.
- Certificate pinning in production via SslPinningInterceptor.

## ProGuard (Android release)
- Keep rules for: Dio, Freezed, json_serializable, Firebase, Supabase, RevenueCat.
- Test release APK before every store submission.
- flutter build apk --release --obfuscate --split-debug-info=build/debug-info

## iOS Security
- NSAppTransportSecurity: no arbitrary loads in production builds.
- App Transport Security exception requires justification in PR.
- PrivacyInfo.xcprivacy required for iOS 17+ API usage.

## secret-guard.sh Hook
- Blocks .env*, .pem, *.key, google-services.json, GoogleService-Info.plist from AI context.
- Fails closed (blocks entire read if secret detected).
